{"word":"μεθύω","slug":"μεθύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μεθύω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μέθυ'><el>μέθυ</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>; the <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> and <a href='S:aorist tense'>aor.</a> <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> belong to <a href='S:μεθύσκω'><el>μεθύσκω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be drunken with wine</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>μ. ὑπὸ τοῦ οἴνου</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of things, <el>βοείη μεθύουσα ἀλοιφῆι</el> an ox-hide <i>soaked</i> in oil, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of persons, <i>to be drunken</i> or <i>intoxicated</i> with passion, pride, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}